Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into small pieces. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in
a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add half the onion and fry
until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Pour the @water{240%ml} for the bulgur wheat
into the pan, stir in half the @vegetable stock paste{1%tbsp} and bring to the
boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for
~{1%minute}. Pop a lid on the saucepan and remove from the heat. Leave to the
side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

While the bulgur cooks, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic
press{}). Trim the @courgette{1}, then slice into thick 1cm rounds. Drain and
rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}. Pop half into a #medium bowl{}
and roughly mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). When hot, add the courgette rounds
and cook until charred, ~{3-4%minutes} each side. Turn only every couple of
minutes - this will result in the courgette picking up some nice colour. Once
cooked, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then chop into roughly 1cm
pieces. Transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and return to medium-high heat with a
drizzle of @oil{}. When hot, add the remaining onion and cook until softened,
~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and chickpeas (both whole and mashed) and cook
for ~{1%minute} more.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1%400g can}, @water{100%ml} for the sauce,
remaining @vegetable stock paste{1%tbsp} and two thirds of the
@harissa paste{33%g} (add less if you don't like heat). Stir together, then
bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Season to taste
with salt and pepper. Bring to the boil, then stir in the @king prawns{150%g}
and cook for a further ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns
> are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

When everything is ready, fluff up the bulgur using a fork and stir through the
remaining @harissa paste{17%g} until well combined. Share the bulgur between
your #bowls{} and top with the harissa prawn stew. Finish with the charred
courgette. Enjoy!